Prueba de la comunicacion de dos procesos de linux a traves de kernel messeges queue. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

build_all.sh:
	Builds server and client. Also, copies the client excecutable into the server's folder.

clean.sh:
	Deletes server's build folder (binary files and cmake generated files) and client binary files.

run.sh:
	MUST BE RUN AS SUPERUSER. Runs server. Client is excecuted within servers code.


For this scripts to run in the beagle the line:
#!/bin/bash -e
must be replaced with:
#!/bin/sh -e
